.TH MWM 1 mwm\-VERSION
.SH NAME
mwm \- matteo's window manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mwm
.RB [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mwm
is a small dynamic tiling window manager for X. It manages windows in two
tiling layouts (equal columns and master+stack) plus floating, with
configurable gaps and optional rounded corners. It draws a translucent,
three\-segment bar (tags+layout, focused title, and status read from the root
window name) and embeds an XEmbed system tray.
.PP
mwm has no built\-in keybindings. All control happens through the
.BR mwmc (1)
client over an X11 ClientMessage IPC channel, so keys are bound externally
(e.g. with sxhkd). Tags form one global pool shared across monitors; each tag
is owned by a single monitor and can be moved between monitors with its
windows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
print version information to stderr, then exit.
.SH USAGE
Start mwm from your
.B ~/.xinitrc :
.PP
.RS
.nf
exec mwm
.fi
.RE
.PP
Control it at runtime:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mwmc focus next
mwmc move win 3
mwmc layout stack
mwmc query state
.fi
.RE
.PP
See
.B mwmc help
for the full command grammar.
.SH CONFIGURATION
mwm is configured by editing
.B config.h
and recompiling. See
.B config.def.h
for the documented defaults.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mwmc (1),
.BR sxhkd (1),
.BR slstatus (1),
.BR picom (1)
